data.title: Alisha Holmes - 2006-07 - Women's Basketball
data.meta_description:
Alisha Holmes (12) G  - 
2005-06 Season: Averaged 2.3 points in 12.8 minutes per game for the year ... recorded four points and three assists in the A-Sun Tournament
data.text:
2005-06 Season: Averaged 2.3 points in 12.8 minutes per game for the year ... recorded four points and three assists in the A-Sun Tournament game against Mercer (3/9/06) ... Had one of her best games of the season at Campbell (3/4/06), posting a career-high five steals to go along with eight points ... pulled down a career-best four rebounds, while adding eight points in the loss at Gardner-Webb (3/2/06) ... also tied a career best for free-throw attempts with six against the Bulldogs ... had three rebounds and two steals in 10 minutes of action against Mercer (2/23/06) ... tied a career high with three rebounds in the loss at Belmont (2/18/06) ... also posted four points in 15 minutes of play against the Bruins ... added four points and four assists in the win at Lipscomb (2/16/06) ... tied her career-high with 10 points in a season-high 24 minutes of play against FAU (1/12/06) ... also posted career highs in field goals (3) and field goal attempts (8) vs. the Owls ... went 4-for-4 from the charity stripe against Appalachian State (12/21/05) ... played 14 minutes in the season opening victory over Mississippi State (11/20/05) ... made her first start of the season at Cincinnati (11/23/05) ... saw two minutes of action against Eastern Kentucky (11/29/05) ... pulled in first rebound of the season against Belmont (12/1/05) ... tallied four points and two assists in eight minutes of play against Lipscomb (12/3/05) ... played 10 minutes at College of Charleston (12/9/05) ... grabbed a rebound in nine minutes of play against Western Kentucky (12/11/05) ... played eight minutes in the win over SEMO (12/28/05) ... dished out a season-best three assists in the win over Kennesaw State (1/2/06) ... posted a career-high six assists, in a season-high 21 minutes of action against North Florida (1/5/06) ... tied season-high with 21 minutes against Jacksonville (1/7/06) ... tallied five assists and four points against the Dolphins ... posted three points, four assists, and a steal in 16 minutes of action at Kennesaw State (1/16/06) ... tallied three points, one assist, and one steal in three minutes against Gardner-Webb (1/21/06) ... totaled two points, three assists, and two steals in 20 minutes of play against Mercer (1/28/06) ... played 12 minutes against FAU (2/4/06), tallying two points, one rebound, and one assist ... collected a rebound and an assist in nine minutes of play against North Florida (2/11/06).

2004-05 Season: Had a career night at Tennessee State , scoring 10 points and dishing out five assists (11/20/04) ... played a career-high 29 minutes at Chattanooga (1/29/05) ... played in 28 games, making one start ... averaged 12.3 minutes per game.

At Orangeburg-Wilkinson H.S.: Four-year letterwinner in women’s basketball and women’s volleyball ... basketball team captain sophomore through senior seasons, garnering most improved accolades sophomore year ... also competed for the Meadowlake Ballers AAU club team.
